status				testing

inherits			gnu

headline			ShockWave Flash movie player
description
	Gnash is a GNU Flash movie player. Previously, it was only possible to play flash movies with proprietary software. While there are some other free flash players, none support anything beyond SWF v4. Gnash is based on GameSWF, and supports many SWF v7 features. It can be run as a graphical application, as a Web browser
plugin, or as a library used by other programs. It is not yet complete; it does not correctly handle every .swf file.
